item.title: Raquel add a quote by Groucho Marx
item.description: "I sent the club a wire stating, PLEASE ACCEPT MY RESIGNATION. I DON'T WANT TO BELONG TO ANY CLUB THAT WILL ACCEPT ME AS A MEMBER." -- Groucho Marx

item.title: Raquel add a quote by Groucho Marx
item.description: "Those are my principles, and if you don't like them...well I have others." -- Groucho Marx

item.title: Raquel add a quote by Ralph Waldo Emerson
item.description: "It is one of the blessings of old friends that you can afford to be stupid with them." -- Ralph Waldo Emerson

item.title: Raquel add a quote by Ralph Waldo Emerson
item.description: "For nonconformity the world will whip you with its displeasure." -- Ralph Waldo Emerson

item.title: Raquel add a quote by Patricia Nell Warren
item.description: "Sooner or later you end up making deals with women. It's an injustice, really." -- Patricia Nell Warren

item.title: Raquel add a quote by Johann wolfgang von Goethe
item.description: "A word spoken is a terrible thing when it suddenly utters what the heart has long allowed." -- Johann wolfgang von Goethe

item.title: Raquel add a quote by Fyodor Dostoevsky
item.description: "Above all, don't lie to yourself. The man who lies to himself and listens to his own lie comes to a point that he cannot distinguish the truth within him, or around him, and so loses all respect for himself and for others. And having no respect he ceases to love." -- Fyodor Dostoevsky
